<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="68" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to
                                Lieutenant General <persName type="to">Albert C.
                                    Wedemeyer</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-17">17 January 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>67. Thanks for your complete statement of demobilization views in 20304.
                            I still would like a concise statement from you to be quoted by me to
                            Generalissimo regarding confusion of understanding which has arisen over
                            your statement to Sixth Army Commander requested in first half of last
                            sentence my 52.<note n="61" xml:id="d68fn61">Telegram of January 15,
                                    <ref target="#pg_189">p. 189</ref>.</note> I do not think it
                            wise to use your 20060 because of reference to armies in third
                            sentence.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>